article.headline: Washington 82, Oregon St. 70
article.story: CORVALLIS, Ore. -- Washington beat Oregon State 82-70 Saturday night, spoiling Senior Day for the Beavers and setting up a rematch between the two schools in the first round of the Pac-10 Conference tournament on Thursday. Matt Bryan-Amaning led the Huskies with 20 points and 11 rebounds. Isaiah Thomas added 19 points and five assists and Quincy Pondexter scored 18 for Washington (21-9, 11-7 Pac-10), which will carry the No. 3 seed in the postseason conference tournament. Roeland Schaftenaar had 15 points for Oregon State (14-16, 8-10), the No. 6 seed in the Pac-10. Washington, which has won six straight games over the Beavers, led 37-29 at the half and by as many as 20 points in the second half. The Huskies had only seven turnovers against the Beavers, who lead the Pac-10 in steals.
